Title : Cuelei River
Text : The '''Cuelei River''' ('''Kwelei'''<ref>{{GEOnet2|32FA88134A593774E0440003BA962ED3|Kwelei (Variant)}}, [[National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency|United States National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency]]</ref>) is a river in central [[Angola]] of southwestern Africa.<ref>{{GEOnet2|32FA88134A5B3774E0440003BA962ED3|Cuelei (Approved)}}, [[National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency|United States National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency]]</ref> For part of its length, it forms the border between [[Bié Province]] to the north and [[Cuando Cubango Province]] to the south.<ref name="SD-33-12">{{Cite map|title=Joint Operations Graphic (Air) SD 33-12, Serpa Pinto, Angola|scale=1:250,000|edition=1 (NIMA reprint April 1999)|publisher=U.S. Army Topographic Command|url=http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/jog/southern_africa/sd-33-12-serpa_pinto-angola.jpg}}</ref> Its major tributary the Cuceque, and its tributary the Missango, also form part of that boundary.<ref name="SD-33-12" />

The Cuelei arises at {{Coord|13|46|51|S|17|51|35|E|display=inline}} in the Anhara-do-Cuelei (Cuelei [[Salt pan (geology)|Salt pan]]),<ref>"anhara" is the name in Angola for the marginal vegetation area on rivers. {{Cite web|title=''Dicionário da Língua Portuguesa - com Acordo Ortográfico'': anhara |publisher=Infopédia|url=http://www.infopedia.pt/lingua-portuguesa/anhara}}</ref> at an elevation of {{Convert|1520|m|ft|-1}}. It flows basically south for its entire length. The Cuelei flows into the Cuchi which flows into the [[Okavango River|Cubango]].<ref name="SD-33-16">{{Cite map|title=Joint Operations Graphic (JOG) SD 33-16, Caiundo, Angola|scale=1:250,000|edition=2|publisher=National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency|}}</ref>

